So we need to show that the set of rational numbers is countable, and hence has Lebesgue measure zero. Then, the set of irrational numbers is the complement of a measure zero set, hence it is comeager. So for all $x \in \mathbb{R}$, $x$ is irrational except on a set of measure zero (the rational numbers).

